The paper deals with fundamental limits of caching in wireless D2D networks, which involves information theory, networking, and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves some aspects of distributed computing, which makes cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with caching of files, which could be considered as a multimedia application, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
